transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes. Hi. My name is Cleveland Long. I put in a prescription there a couple days ago. I've gotten emails saying that it was all approved and all that, but I haven't got an updated email telling me when it was shipped.

Speaker 1: Okay. What's your zip code, please?

Speaker 2: The zip code for what, the building or where it's being delivered?

Speaker 1: Either one.

Speaker 2: 04769.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Okay. 64 Broadway in Baileyville, Maine is where it's shipping to?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me see what's going on here. Yeah, you've been approved. It should ship out tomorrow. I don't know why you haven't been updated about that, but I'm going to message the pharmacy just to make sure it goes out tomorrow.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Once it does, I can follow up and send you a tracking.

Speaker 2: Perfect. Thank you very much, sir.

Speaker 1: Of course. I hope you have a great evening.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye-bye.
